title: Singapore Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Singapore Three Month Interbank Rate was at 3.98 percent on Thursday November 10. Interbank Rate in Singapore averaged 1.65 percent from 1995 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 9.84 percent in January of 1998 and a record low of 0.34 percent in September of 2011. In Singapore, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Singapore Three Month Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Development Bank of Singapore
